OL,4,Cprevent abuse at notorious detention
OL,5,Ccentre
OL,7,FPowerfully-built Husband was thought
OL,8,Fto have groomed and attacked hundreds
OL,9,Fof trainees in Medomsley's kitchens.
OL,11,FHe was finally convicted of sexual
OL,12,Fassault and was jailed in 2003 and
OL,13,Fagain in 2005. He died in 2010.
OL,15,FMr Usher stated: "The illegitimate
OL,16,Fpower imbalance that existed between
OL,17,FHusband and the trainees and other
OL,18,Fstaff further flourished within a
OL,19,Fculture of collusion and silence from
OL,20,Fother employees.
OL,26,@wD@ROU
