OL,3,CReport damning of state failures to
OL,4,Cprevent abuse at notorious detention
OL,5,Ccentre
OL,7,FCruelty was evident in Medomsley's
OL,8,Fmedical centre until the 1970s, the
OL,9,Freport stated, with a number of
OL,10,Fwitnesses saying if they were ill,
OL,11,Fpainkillers could be taped to their
OL,12,Fforehead and they would be told to run
OL,13,Faround until the pill had dissolved.
OL,15,FMr Usher found that oversight of the
OL,16,Fcentre by external bodies was poor and
OL,17,Fif family members made complaints
OL,18,Fabout their loved ones' treatment,
OL,19,Fnothing happened.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G9/12
